ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC BOOLRULE <options>; 
    DOCINFO <options>; 
    TERMINFO <options>; 
    OUTPUT <options>; 
    SCORE <options>; 

The BOOLRULE procedure is a SAS Viya procedure that enables you to extract Boolean rules from large-scale 
transactional data. 

The BOOLRULE procedure can automatically generate a set of Boolean rules by analyzing a text corpus that 
has been processed by the TEXTMINE procedure and is represented in a transactional format.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: DOCINFO <options>;

The DOCINFO statement specifies information about the data table that is specified in the DOCINFO= 
option in the PROC BOOLRULE statement.

Syntax: SCORE <options>;

The SCORE statement specifies the input data table that contains the terms in rules and the output 
data table to contain the scoring results.
